-- GM to invest $332 million in Ohio plant
-- 
-- Fri May 18, 2007 2:29pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/05/18/us-gm-toledo-idUSWEN824720070518

 

 DETROIT  (Reuters) - General Motors Corp ( GM.N ) said on Friday it plans to invest $332 million in its Toledo, Ohio plant to make a new six-speed, front-wheel drive transmission. 

 The investment includes plant renovation, new machinery, equipment and special tooling. GM said it will also invest an additional $57 million at other locations necessary to support the Toledo operations.